  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "「ポートピア連続殺人事件」は、ドラゴンクエストの著名なゲームデザイナー、堀井雄二のゲーム業界へのデビュー作です。この作品は、第一人称視点のミステリー・テキストアドベンチャーで、1983年にPC-6001システム向けに最初に発売されました。NES版では、プレイヤーはゲームパッドを使って動詞リストからコマンドを選択し、画面上のグラフィックを調べてホットスポットを探すことができます。\n\n物語は、無名の日本の警察探偵となったプレイヤーが、銀行の取締役の殺人事件を解決するための旅に出るというものです。実在の日本の風景を巡る中で、無名で無口な主人公は、彼の指示を実行する同僚のヤスに助けられます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "An investigation adventure in which the player, acting as an unnamed Japanese detective, is called to solve the murder of a bank executive by searching for clues, exploring different areas, interacting with characters, and solving item-based puzzles. The game, especially its Famicom version, was received positively in Japan, where it was an influential title that defined the visual novel genre, as well as inspiring future designers such as Hideo Kojima and paving the way for creator Yuji Horii to go on to make Dragon Quest series of role-playing games.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "Kouzou Yamakawa, the president of the Loan and Savings Company, was found dead inside his mansion. A detective and his assistant arrive at the scene for further investigation. The player must resolve the mystery of a murder by searching for clues, interacting with characters, and solving item-based puzzles.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
